# Single-database configuration for Flask

To connect to the database (in this case, pgAdmin), create a `.env` file in the project root:

```
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg2://<username>:<password>@localhost:5432/<your_db_name>

FLASK_APP=app:create_app
FLASK_ENV=development
```

When you modify your models, run:

```
# To produce a migration script:
flask db migrate -m "comment message"

# To apply the migration and create tables:
flask db upgrade
```